<subSubSection id="C37500CDFFBEF058F853F4CB11EAF3A0" pageId="4" pageNumber="347" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD05346FFBEF058F853F4CB11EAF3A0" blockId="4.[2017,2603,2759,3177]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">
Flerov, when he described this species, regarded it as an enigmatic species of apparently restricted distribution in the alpine zone of 
<collectingRegion id="49AB9DA4FFBEF058F7E0F44511AAF46D" box="[2129,2243,2947,2980]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
. It was not until the 1960s that it was shown that this is not in fact an alpine zone species at all, but is a forest animal, widespread in the forested areas of south-eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F37813D6FFBEF058F76BF3E61059F388" box="[2266,2352,3104,3137]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">China</collectingCountry>
. Four subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
